President Barack Obama has proclaimed June 2012 as Great Outdoors Month in the United States. In his proclamation, he highlights the importance of America's natural treasures and landscapes in reflecting the country's national character. He acknowledges the role of past leaders and citizens in preserving natural beauty and announces initiatives aimed at reconnecting Americans with the natural world and promoting a more sustainable planet. These initiatives include the America's Great Outdoors Initiative, the 21st Century Conservation Service Corps, and First Lady Michelle Obama's Let's Move Outside! campaign. President Obama also emphasizes the economic benefits of protecting the environment, such as the contributions of visitors to local economies. He encourages all Americans to celebrate their natural heritage by engaging in outdoor activities and upholding the legacy of conserving lands and waters for future generations.